Content:: The suprainiac fossa is an elliptical depression on the occiput above the superior nuchal line, or inion, or a dent in the back of the head. Suprainiac fossae were common anatomical features of Neanderthals but are rare in modern Humans.[1][2]  This human musculoskeletal system article is a stub. You can help Wikipedia by expanding it.
